author: STAFF REPORT
title: Sports - The Times-Tribune
text:

Lakeland graduate Michael Thomas shot an even-par 72 and finished in third place overall with a two-day score of 146 (+2), as Marywood University finished tied for second at the ECAC Mid-Atlantic Fall Championships at Ravenwood Golf Club in Victor, New York. 
The Pacers had a four-stroke lead for second place over New York University after Saturday’s first round but Dalton Deardorff self-reported having too many clubs in his bag and was assessed a two-stroke penalty on each of the first two holes. Deardorff originally shot 77 on Saturday but the penalty resulted in him shooting a 9-over 81. 
Along with Thomas, Jesse Bingaman also shot 72 on Sunday and finished with a two-day total of 151 (+7), good enough for 10th place. 
Marywood and NYU both finished with a score of 617, while St. John Fisher won the team title with 583. St. John Fisher also had the top two individual finishers, as Karl Deuble won with a two-day total of 142 (-2) and Corey Haas was second with 145 (+1). 
Men’s tennis 
The University of Scranton lost its only match of the fall season, 9-0, to Wilkes University. 
The Royals will return to action during the spring semester.
